\name{plot.DBEST}
\alias{plot.DBEST}
%- Also NEED an '\alias' for EACH other topic documented here.
\title{
Methods for objects of class "DBEST".
}
\description{
Plot methods for objects of class "DBEST".
}
\usage{
%%## S3 method for class 'DBEST':
\method{plot}{DBEST}(x, figure = 1, ...)
}
%- maybe also 'usage' for other objects documented here.
\arguments{
  \item{x}{
DBEST object.
}
  \item{figure}{
If omited, the plot function will display 'figure 1' and 'figure 2'. If this option is set to 1, the plot function
will display the input data and the estimated trend, plus the trend local change (figure 1). If this option is set to 2, 
the plot function will display a graph with the decomposition of the time-series, including the actual data, the trend, 
the seasonal component and the reminder.
}
  \item{...}{further arguments passed to the \code{\link[graphics]{plot}} function.}
}

\author{
Hristo Tomov
}

